## Location
firmware/bridge-zephyr/subsys/lichen/lichen_l2.c:324-329

## Finding
```c
size_t pkt_len = net_pkt_get_len(pkt);
if (pkt_len > sizeof(tx_ipv6_buf)) {
    LOG_ERR("Packet too large: %zu > %zu", pkt_len, sizeof(tx_ipv6_buf));
    return -EMSGSIZE;
}
```

This is actually CORRECT code. The comparison is between two `size_t` values.

**Not an issue** - marking this as a non-finding for documentation purposes.

Actually, let me verify the buffer sizing more carefully. `tx_ipv6_buf` is `LICHEN_L2_MTU + IPV6_BASE_HDR_LEN` = 200 + 40 = 240 bytes. The IPv6 stack should not send packets larger than LICHEN_L2_MTU (200), and 200 + 40 = 240 bytes is the theoretical max including header.
